      </p>
      <p>
        Methodologically, I primarily employ <span class="text-orange-900 font-bold">quantitative</span> methods to analyze large-scale survey and administrative data. I also conduct exploratory work on <span class="text-orange-900 font-bold">computational</span> approaches to better understand the mechanisms underlying work, family, and health.
      </p>
      <p>
        My recent research interests include: working time mismatch; time use and sequence analysis; generative AI in the social sciences.
      </p>
